{"title":"Sombrio expands their clothing line… by adding complete mountain bikes!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/07/sombrio-expands-their-clothing-line-by-adding-complete-mountain-bikes/","date":1631042504000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-270772\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>British Columbia’s Sombrio is a well-established clothing brand in the MTB world, but they’ve just made a major shift. Now they’ve jumped into the bike game with four new hardtail mountain bikes. Furthermore, Sombrio also has their own branded components for the bikes, including handlebars, seat posts, stems, and saddles.</p><p>Sombrio’s bikes are called the Shovel 2, 3, 4 and 5, with ‘2’ being the highest-end build and ‘5’ serving as the entry model. The four bikes are all within an entry-level price range, selling for $730-$1300 CAD (please note the bikes are currently only shown on the Canadian website).</p><h2>Sombrio Shovel frame details:</h2><h2><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144629/Sombrio-Shovel-3-trailside.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144629/Sombrio-Shovel-3-trailside.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:780x521/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" alt=\"Sombrio Shovel 3 hardtail MTB, trailside\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144629/Sombrio-Shovel-3-trailside.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144629/Sombrio-Shovel-3-trailside-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144629/Sombrio-Shovel-3-trailside-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144629/Sombrio-Shovel-3-trailside-768x513.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144629/Sombrio-Shovel-3-trailside.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:780x521/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" ezoid=\"0.3289521289985877\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144629/Sombrio-Shovel-3-trailside.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144629/Sombrio-Shovel-3-trailside-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144629/Sombrio-Shovel-3-trailside-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144629/Sombrio-Shovel-3-trailside-768x513.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w\"></a></h2><p>There are some similarities and some differences between the frames on the various Shovels, so let’s dig in to the details: First off, all models of the Shovel are made from 6061 T6 Aluminum, and roll on 27.5” wheels.</p><p>Wheel spacing gets a bit interesting; The entry model Shovel 5 offers 10×135 rear spacing, mated to 9x100mm forks. The Shovel 4 and 3 both have 10x141mm rear spacing (Boost QR), but the Shovel 4 has a 9x100mm fork while the 3 gets a Boost-spaced 15x110mm fork. The top model Shovel 2 offers Boost 148mm rear spacing, and a 15x110mm Boost fork.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144641/Sombrio-Shovel-front-end.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144641/Sombrio-Shovel-front-end.jpg\" alt=\"Sombrio Shovel 3, front end\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144641/Sombrio-Shovel-front-end.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144641/Sombrio-Shovel-front-end-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144641/Sombrio-Shovel-front-end-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144641/Sombrio-Shovel-front-end-768x513.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144641/Sombrio-Shovel-front-end.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144641/Sombrio-Shovel-front-end.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144641/Sombrio-Shovel-front-end-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144641/Sombrio-Shovel-front-end-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144641/Sombrio-Shovel-front-end-768x513.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>Not all head tubes are equal either; The Shovel 5 frame comes with a straight 1-1/8” head tube, but all other models get a tapered type. The specs reveal the Shovel 4 comes with a straight 1-1/8<sup>th</sup> fork (but it’s nice the frame allows for upgrades). Other fitments include 73mm bottom brackets, and 31.6mm seat posts.</p><p>Brake and derailleur cables are both externally routed, but Sombrio has included internal cable routing for dropper posts, and two water bottle mounts on the down tube. All models offer S/M/L frame sizes, and each model gets one frame color only.</p><h3><strong>Geometry:</strong></h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144644/Sombrio-Shovel-hardtail-geo-chart.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144644/Sombrio-Shovel-hardtail-geo-chart.jpg\" alt=\"Sombrio Shovel frame geometry\" width=\"591\" height=\"673\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144644/Sombrio-Shovel-hardtail-geo-chart.jpg 591w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144644/Sombrio-Shovel-hardtail-geo-chart-263x300.jpg 263w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144644/Sombrio-Shovel-hardtail-geo-chart-105x120.jpg 105w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 591px) 100vw, 591px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144644/Sombrio-Shovel-hardtail-geo-chart.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144644/Sombrio-Shovel-hardtail-geo-chart.jpg 591w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144644/Sombrio-Shovel-hardtail-geo-chart-263x300.jpg 263w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144644/Sombrio-Shovel-hardtail-geo-chart-105x120.jpg 105w\"></a></p><p>The Shovel frames all share the same geometry. All the figures are pretty up-to-date but not extreme. They have 66° head tubes, 74° seat masts, and 430mm chainstays across all sizes. Reach numbers are 430/450/470mm for S/M/L.</p><h3><strong>Model Lineup:</strong></h3><p><strong>Shovel 2:</strong></p><div id=\"attachment_270777\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144638/Sombrio-Shovel-berm.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-270777\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144638/Sombrio-Shovel-berm.jpg\" alt=\"Sombrio Shovel, berm\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144638/Sombrio-Shovel-berm.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144638/Sombrio-Shovel-berm-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144638/Sombrio-Shovel-berm-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144638/Sombrio-Shovel-berm-768x513.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144638/Sombrio-Shovel-berm.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144638/Sombrio-Shovel-berm.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144638/Sombrio-Shovel-berm-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144638/Sombrio-Shovel-berm-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144638/Sombrio-Shovel-berm-768x513.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-270777\">*Sombrio didn’t have any photos available of the complete Shovel 2, so here’s a nice berm railing pic for you!</p></div><p>The top-of-the-line Shovel 2 offers a 140mm travel Uding UD34 Air-Boost fork, which can be locked out. It rolls on Torngat alloy rims and Caribou T15 and T12 hubs, wrapped with 2.6” wide CST BFT tires. It’s 10-speed drivetrain is supplied by Microshift, and you get a KS E-20i dropper post on this model (125mm on smalls, 150mm on medium and large frames).</p><p>The Shovel 2 also comes with hydraulic Riderever disc brakes on 180/160mm rotors. Sombrio finishes things off with their own Loam saddle, handlebar, and 45mm stem. &nbsp;The Shovel 2 sells for $1299.99 CAD, and comes in Ceramic Grey.</p><p><strong>Shovel 3:</strong></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144626/Sombrio-Shovel-3-hardtail-side.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144626/Sombrio-Shovel-3-hardtail-side.jpg\" alt=\"Sombrio Shovel 3, side\" width=\"800\" height=\"493\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144626/Sombrio-Shovel-3-hardtail-side.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144626/Sombrio-Shovel-3-hardtail-side-297x183.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144626/Sombrio-Shovel-3-hardtail-side-120x74.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144626/Sombrio-Shovel-3-hardtail-side-768x473.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144626/Sombrio-Shovel-3-hardtail-side.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144626/Sombrio-Shovel-3-hardtail-side.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144626/Sombrio-Shovel-3-hardtail-side-297x183.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144626/Sombrio-Shovel-3-hardtail-side-120x74.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144626/Sombrio-Shovel-3-hardtail-side-768x473.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>Up front on the Shovel 3 is a 140mm Uding UD D5 Coil-Boost fork, which also offers a lockout. It runs on Torngat rims and Caribou Hubs, and also gets beefy 2.6” CST tires. The 9-speed drivetrain is all Microshift components, and braking is handled by Riderever Attack hydraulic discs with 180/160mm rotors.</p><p>Sombrio’s seat, bars, stem and seat post all appear on the Shovel 3. This model comes in Black Bear, and sells for $999.99 CAD.</p><p><strong>Shovel 4:</strong></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144632/Sombrio-Shovel-4-hardtail-angle.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144632/Sombrio-Shovel-4-hardtail-angle.jpg\" alt=\"Sombrio Shovel 4, angle\" width=\"800\" height=\"700\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144632/Sombrio-Shovel-4-hardtail-angle.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144632/Sombrio-Shovel-4-hardtail-angle-297x260.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144632/Sombrio-Shovel-4-hardtail-angle-120x105.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144632/Sombrio-Shovel-4-hardtail-angle-768x672.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144632/Sombrio-Shovel-4-hardtail-angle.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144632/Sombrio-Shovel-4-hardtail-angle.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144632/Sombrio-Shovel-4-hardtail-angle-297x260.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144632/Sombrio-Shovel-4-hardtail-angle-120x105.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144632/Sombrio-Shovel-4-hardtail-angle-768x672.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>Sombrio’s Shovel 4 stocks a lockable, 120mm travel Uding UD D5 Coil fork. For wheels, it gets the Torngat rim/Caribou hub combo, with CST’s 2.6” BFT treads. The 4 runs an 8-speed Microshift drivetrain, but it offers a fairly wide range with an 11-46t cassette. Riderever’s hydraulic Attack disc brakes reel you in, and Sombrio’s components round out the build.</p><p>The Shovel 4 retails for $849.99 CAD, and is painted Pine Green.</p><p><strong>Shovel 5:</strong></p><div id=\"attachment_270776\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144635/Sombrio-Shovel-5-hardtail-side.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-270776\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144635/Sombrio-Shovel-5-hardtail-side.jpg\" alt=\"Sombrio Shovel 5, side\" width=\"800\" height=\"502\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144635/Sombrio-Shovel-5-hardtail-side.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144635/Sombrio-Shovel-5-hardtail-side-297x186.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144635/Sombrio-Shovel-5-hardtail-side-120x75.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144635/Sombrio-Shovel-5-hardtail-side-768x482.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144635/Sombrio-Shovel-5-hardtail-side.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144635/Sombrio-Shovel-5-hardtail-side.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144635/Sombrio-Shovel-5-hardtail-side-297x186.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144635/Sombrio-Shovel-5-hardtail-side-120x75.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/07144635/Sombrio-Shovel-5-hardtail-side-768x482.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-270776\">*Images c. Sombrio Cartel</p></div><p>The entry-point Shovel 5 comes with a 130mm RST Blaze Coil fork, and Torngat alloy rims and Caribou Co. hubs with 2.25” CST BFT tires. This model offers a 1×9 drivetrain with a 30t narrow-wide chainring up front. The brakes are Jak ZJ-5 mechanical discs on 180/160mm rotors. Sombrio supplies the handlebar, stem, seat post and Loam saddle.</p><p>The Shovel 5 comes in Commando Green. MSRP is $729.99 CAD.</p><p>Sombrio’s Shovel hardtails will not be sold online, and are currently only available through their Canadian dealers. Check out their website’s dealer locator to find one near you.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.sombriocartel.com/en-CA\"><em>sombriocartel.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Steve Fisher","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"04c19c5623c04e80dd21bee1b52d6aef4ba770808759b144a771ae5e2ee8f5be","category":"Cycling"}